        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A ring of eight dragon pillar replicas mark the border of a dome of magical prismatic energy that entirely contains the Fortress of Sorrow.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>Each dragon pillar that is destroyed removes the corresponding color's effect from Dahak's shell; as long as even one color remains active, the pillars marking the shell's border cannot be damaged themselves, but a successful <span data-pf2-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-traits=\"magical,trap,hazard\" data-pf2-label=\"Disable Color DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"32\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> (master) check or a successful <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dispel Magic]{Dispel Magic}</em> (6th level; counteract DC 30) against one of the eight pillars can cause a randomly determined active color in the shell defense (below) to become deactivated for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>",
